## Converting Between Loops

Under the hood, `for` loops and `while` loops do the exact same thing! You can always write a `for` loop as a `while` loop if you wanted to.

### Here is a For loop:
```javascript
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```

### Here is the exact same logic as a While loop:
```javascript
let i = 0; // The 'start' moves above the loop
while (i < 5) { // The 'condition' goes in the ()
  console.log(i);
  i++; // The 'step' moves to the end of the block
}
```
